Van Dale Pocketwoordenboeken is an excellent set of Dutch dictionaries for anyone interested in the Dutch language. It gives numerous usage examples as well as definitions. Van Dale has broken up the dictionaries now and sells them separately. This compact four language program is no longer sold and is only available by bittorrent. Armed with these dictionaries and Yahoo's Babelfish service, I have been able to make serviceable translations from Dutch to English with relative ease. Thanks, Van Dale, for a terrific product!
